ibm3172MIB.description: The MIB module for managing an IBM 3172 Device that has is running ICP.

ibm3172Descr.name: ibm3172Descr
ibm3172Descr.description: Text Description of the 3172. Contains information on the hardware and software of the 3172. The format of the ibm3172Descr variable is : ttttxMODELxmmm,xSERIALxNUMBERxsssssssss,xiiiiiiiiiix 111111,xPROGRAMxNUMBERxpppppp where : x represents a blank character upper case letters are hardcoded characters , represents a comma the remaining lower case letters represent variable data as follows: t - machine type m - model number s - serial number i - software program name l - software level numbers p - software program product number. An example of the information sent with this attribute would be : '3172 MODEL 001, SERIAL NUMBER 000001234, 3172 Interconnect Ctlr Program 020100, 5601433'

ibm3172Contact.name: ibm3172Contact
ibm3172Contact.description: The textual identification of the contact person for this 3172, together with information on how to contact this person. This information is provided by the 3172 Operator Facility.

ibm3172Location.name: ibm3172Location
ibm3172Location.description: The physical location of this node. This information is provided by the 3172 Operator Facility.

ibm3172ifNumber.name: ibm3172ifNumber
ibm3172ifNumber.description: The number of interfaces (regardless of their current state) on which this 3172 can send data.

ibm3172ifTrapTable.name: ibm3172ifTrapTable
ibm3172ifTrapTable.description: Table of objects at the interface level pertaining to the trap function.

ibm3172ifTrapTableEntry.name: ibm3172ifTrapTableEntry
ibm3172ifTrapTableEntry.description: Objects at the interface level pertaining to the trap function.

ibm3172ifTrapEnable.name: ibm3172ifTrapEnable
ibm3172ifTrapEnable.description: Flag to indicate whether the 3172 should send traps for this interface to the SNMP proxy agent. '0' indicates the trap function of the 3172 is disabled, '1' indicates that it is enabled.

ibm3172ifChanCountersTable.name: ibm3172ifChanCountersTable
ibm3172ifChanCountersTable.description: Table of objects at the subnetwork layer and below pertaining to a particular subchannel of the 3172.

ibm3172ifChanCountersTableEntry.name: ibm3172ifChanCountersTableEntry
ibm3172ifChanCountersTableEntry.description: Objects at the subnetwork layer and below pertaining to a particular subchannel of the 3172.

ibm3172ifInChanOctets.name: ibm3172ifInChanOctets
ibm3172ifInChanOctets.description: The number of inbound octets which were transmitted to the host by the 3172, including all headers.

ibm3172ifOutChanOctets.name: ibm3172ifOutChanOctets
ibm3172ifOutChanOctets.description: The number of outbound octets which were received from the host by the 3172, including all headers.

ibm3172ifInChanBlocks.name: ibm3172ifInChanBlocks
ibm3172ifInChanBlocks.description: The number of inbound blocks which were transmitted to the host by the 3172.

ibm3172ifOutChanBlocks.name: ibm3172ifOutChanBlocks
ibm3172ifOutChanBlocks.description: The number of outbound blocks which were received from the host by the 3172.

ibm3172ifLANCountersTable.name: ibm3172ifLANCountersTable
ibm3172ifLANCountersTable.description: Table of objects at the subnetwork layer and below pertaining to a particular LAN of the 3172.

ibm3172ifLANCountersTableEntry.name: ibm3172ifLANCountersTableEntry
ibm3172ifLANCountersTableEntry.description: Objects at the subnetwork layer and below pertaining to a particular LAN of the 3172.

ibm3172ifInLANOctets.name: ibm3172ifInLANOctets
ibm3172ifInLANOctets.description: The number of inbound octets which were received from the LAN by the 3172, including all headers.

ibm3172ifOutLANOctets.name: ibm3172ifOutLANOctets
ibm3172ifOutLANOctets.description: The number of outbound octets which were transmitted to the LAN by the 3172, including all headers.

ibm3172ifInLANFrames.name: ibm3172ifInLANFrames
ibm3172ifInLANFrames.description: The number of inbound frames which were received from the LAN by the 3172.

ibm3172ifOutLANFrames.name: ibm3172ifOutLANFrames
ibm3172ifOutLANFrames.description: The number of outbound frames which were transmitted to the LAN by the 3172.

ibm3172ifInLANErrors.name: ibm3172ifInLANErrors
ibm3172ifInLANErrors.description: The number of inbound frames received from the LAN by the 3172 that contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher layer protocol. This variable, when combined with ibm3172ifInBlkErrors, reflects the total number of inbound frames not forwarded from the LAN to the host because of errors.

ibm3172ifOutLANErrors.name: ibm3172ifOutLANErrors
ibm3172ifOutLANErrors.description: The number of outbound frames that could not be transmitted to the LAN because of transmission failures. This variable, when combined with ibm3172ifOutDblkErrors, reflects the total number of outbound frames not transmitted to the LAN because of transmission errors.

ibm3172ifInLANDiscards.name: ibm3172ifInLANDiscards
ibm3172ifInLANDiscards.description: The number of inbound frames received from the LAN that were discarded by the 3172, even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a frame could be because of insufficient buffer space. This variable, when combined with ibm3172ifInBlkDiscards, reflects the total number of inbound frames not forwarded from the LAN when no error was detected.

ibm3172ifOutLANDiscards.name: ibm3172ifOutLANDiscards
ibm3172ifOutLANDiscards.description: The number of outbound frames that are discarded.

ibm3172ifBlkCountersTable.name: ibm3172ifBlkCountersTable
ibm3172ifBlkCountersTable.description: Table of objects at the Subnetwork layer and below pertaining to a particular Blocker Task of the 3172.

ibm3172ifBlkCountersTableEntry.name: ibm3172ifBlkCountersTableEntry
ibm3172ifBlkCountersTableEntry.description: Objects at the Subnetwork layer and below pertaining to a particular Blocker Task of the 3172.

ibm3172ifBlkRcvOctets.name: ibm3172ifBlkRcvOctets
ibm3172ifBlkRcvOctets.description: The number of inbound octets which were received by the Blocker from the LAN, including all headers.

ibm3172ifBlkXmitOctets.name: ibm3172ifBlkXmitOctets
ibm3172ifBlkXmitOctets.description: The number of inbound octets which were transmitted to the channel adapter by the Blocker, including all headers.

ibm3172ifBlkRcvFrames.name: ibm3172ifBlkRcvFrames
ibm3172ifBlkRcvFrames.description: The number of inbound frames which were received from the LAN adapter by the Blocker Task.

ibm3172ifBlkXmitBlocks.name: ibm3172ifBlkXmitBlocks
ibm3172ifBlkXmitBlocks.description: The number of inbound blocks which were transmitted to the channel adapter by the blocker task.

ibm3172ifInBlkErrors.name: ibm3172ifInBlkErrors
ibm3172ifInBlkErrors.description: The number of inbound frames transmitted by the LAN adapter to the Blocker Task which contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher layer protocol. This variable, when combined with ibm3172ifInLANErrors, reflects the total number of inbound frames discarded by the 3172 because of errors.

ibm3172ifInBlkDiscards.name: ibm3172ifInBlkDiscards
ibm3172ifInBlkDiscards.description: The number of inbound frames transmitted by the LAN adapter to the Blocker Task which were discarded by the 3172, even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher layer protocol. One possible reason for discarding such a frame could be because of insufficient buffer space. This variable, when combined with ibm3172ifInLANDiscards, reflects the total number of inbound frames discarded by the 3172 when no error was detected.

ibm3172ifDblkCountersTable.name: ibm3172ifDblkCountersTable
ibm3172ifDblkCountersTable.description: Table of objects at the subnetwork layer and below pertaining to a particular Deblocker Task of the 3172.

ibm3172ifDblkCountersTableEntry.name: ibm3172ifDblkCountersTableEntry
ibm3172ifDblkCountersTableEntry.description: Objects at the subnetwork layer and below pertaining to a particular Deblocker Task of the 3172.

ibm3172ifDblkRcvOctets.name: ibm3172ifDblkRcvOctets
ibm3172ifDblkRcvOctets.description: The number of outbound octets which were received by the Deblocker from the channel adapter, including all headers.

ibm3172ifDblkXmitOctets.name: ibm3172ifDblkXmitOctets
ibm3172ifDblkXmitOctets.description: The number of outbound octets which were transmitted to the LAN adapter by the Deblocker, including all headers.

ibm3172ifDblkRcvBlocks.name: ibm3172ifDblkRcvBlocks
ibm3172ifDblkRcvBlocks.description: The number of outbound blocks which were received from the channel adapter by the deblocker task.

ibm3172ifDblkXmitFrames.name: ibm3172ifDblkXmitFrames
ibm3172ifDblkXmitFrames.description: The number of outbound frames which were transmitted to the LAN adapter by the Deblocker Task.

ibm3172ifOutDblkErrors.name: ibm3172ifOutDblkErrors
ibm3172ifOutDblkErrors.description: The number of outbound frames transmitted by the channel adapter to the Deblocker Task which contained errors preventing them from being deliverable to a higher layer protocol. This variable, when combined with ibm3172ifOutLANErrors, reflects the total number of outbound frames discarded by the 3172 because of errors.

ibm3172ifOutDblkDiscards.name: ibm3172ifOutDblkDiscards
ibm3172ifOutDblkDiscards.description: The number of outbound frames transmitted by the channel adapter to the Deblocker Task which were discarded by the 3172, even though no errors had been detected to prevent their being deliverable to a higher layer protocol . One possible reason for discarding such a frame could be because of insufficient buffer space. This variable reflects the total number of outbound frames discarded by the 3172 when no error was detected.

ibm3172ifDeviceNumber.name: ibm3172ifDeviceNumber
ibm3172ifDeviceNumber.description: The instance number, used to reference the ibm3172SystemTable, for the device associated with this interface.

ibm3172MIBCompliance.name: ibm3172MIBCompliance
ibm3172MIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities which implement the IBM3172 MIB.

ibm3172Group.name: ibm3172Group
ibm3172Group.description: The ibm3172 group of objects providing for basic management of of an IBM 3172 device running ICP.
